          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: long-form blog content is weak</h4><p>Articles generated by Copy.ai consistently need more editing than Jasper or Letterdrop output. Not the right pick if blog content is your primary channel.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-7" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#7 · CUSTOM PRICING · 5/6 PIPELINE STEPS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Contently — Best enterprise content operations platform</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For enterprise content teams that need a vetted freelancer network, editorial workflow, content analytics, and CMS publishing — with a six-figure budget to match.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Contently is the original enterprise content platform. It connects brands with vetted freelance journalists, manages the editorial workflow from brief to publish, tracks content performance, and integrates with major CMS platforms. The quality bar is high — Contently's freelancer network produces genuinely excellent work. The budget requirement ($40,000+/year) makes it inaccessible for small businesses.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Vetted freelancer network with category expertise</h4><p>Contently's writer marketplace matches briefs to writers with industry-specific experience. The quality differential vs. generic freelancer platforms is real.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Content analytics with revenue attribution</h4><p>One of the few platforms that tracks content from publication to pipeline influence. Useful for enterprise teams that need to justify content ROI.</p></div></li>
