        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="service-8" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#8 · $89–$219/MO · 2/6 PIPELINE STEPS</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Surfer SEO — Best content optimization layer for existing workflows</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For writers and SEO teams who already have a content production process and need a scoring layer that tells them exactly what to add before publishing.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Surfer doesn't write content or publish it — but it makes the content you write dramatically more likely to rank. The Content Editor scores your article 0–100 as you write, surfacing NLP terms extracted from the top 10–20 ranking pages for your target keyword. The audit tool applies the same logic to existing published pages. Two of six pipeline steps, but those two are the highest-leverage optimization steps.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Best NLP scoring and SERP-based content recommendations</h4><p>The content scoring is the most reliable in the category. Articles scoring 70+ on Surfer consistently outperform unoptimized content on the same keyword.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Topical map feature for content strategy</h4><p>Identifies content clusters for a topic — which articles to write first, how to build topical authority systematically.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Integrates with Google Docs, WordPress, and Jasper</h4><p>Works inside your existing workflow without forcing a platform switch.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: narrow automation scope</h4><p>Only handles optimization and (with the Topical Map) some research. You still need writers, a brief process, and a publishing workflow. It's a component — not a pipeline.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

