      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is an automated content workflow tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">An automated content workflow tool eliminates manual handoffs between research, writing, editing, SEO optimization, and CMS publishing. The best tools move content through multiple pipeline steps automatically — so a blog post goes from keyword research to live on your site without a human transferring it between platforms.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best fully automated content workflow tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is the only tool that covers all 6 pipeline steps — research, brief, write, edit, optimize, and publish — with zero manual handoffs. At $99/month for 30 published articles, it costs less than a single freelance article while delivering more output than most full content teams.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How many workflow steps do most content tools automate?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Most tools automate 2–4 of the 6 steps. Letterdrop and Contently automate 5 but still require editorial approval. Jasper and Copy.ai handle 3. Only theStacc covers all 6 with zero handoffs — content publishes to your CMS without you touching it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can automated content workflow tools publish directly to WordPress?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. theStacc, Letterdrop, CoSchedule, HubSpot Content Hub, and Contently all support direct WordPress publishing. theStacc also publishes to Webflow, Ghost, and custom webhooks. Tools like Jasper and Surfer SEO do not publish — they require you to manually copy content into your CMS.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much does a full content workflow automation stack cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Building a DIY stack costs $49–$300/month in tools plus $150+ per article in freelance writing. A 30-article/month operation runs $4,500–$8,000/month. theStacc replaces the entire stack for $99/month — saving most businesses $40,000+ per year.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between a content workflow tool and a content creation tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Content creation tools (Jasper, Copy.ai) generate text but leave optimization, distribution, and publishing to you. Content workflow tools handle the full production pipeline — from brief to live article. The key metric is how many handoffs you still need to manage manually after using the tool.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What should I look for in a content workflow tool?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Evaluate pipeline coverage (how many of the 6 steps it handles), handoff reduction (does content move automatically between steps?), CMS integration (can it publish directly to your site?), output quality (can the final content rank without heavy revision?), and cost per published article — not cost per month.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
